text: Karl Albert Staaff, born 21 January 1860, dead 4 October 1915, was a Swedish liberal politician and lawyer. He was the chairman of the Liberal Coalition Party between 1907-1915. He served twice as the Prime Minister of Sweden, first between 1905-1906 and then again between 1911-1914. == References == Category:1860 births Category:1915 deaths Category:Government ministers of Sweden Category:Swedish lawyers Category:Politicians from Stockholm Category:Prime ministers of Sweden
